      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 1276: The `fetched` status is updated asynchronously: `Conversation::hasFetched()` dispatches the status update onto `dht::ThreadPool::io()` (conversation.cpp:2673). `removeGitSocket` is also invoked from the git socket\u0027s `onShutdown` on the same io pool (jamiaccount.cpp:2566-2570), and `resendMessageNotificationIfUnfetched` itself re-dispatches onto that pool. There is therefore no ordering guarantee between the fetched-status write and this check. In the common, healthy case (remote device fetches the last commit and then disconnects), the status may not yet be recorded when this runs, so the guard reports \u0027unfetched\u0027 and fires a redundant re-announce with device `{}` — waking the member\u0027s devices over DHT/push on every normal disconnect. Consider deferring the check slightly, or re-verifying the fetched status after a short delay, to avoid spurious wake-ups.",
